Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper presents a logic model for abstract figures using set theory and gives two logic systems for graph traversal and coloring. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as the paper deals with graph theory and algorithms for graph partitioning and coloring. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper presents algorithms for graph traversal and coloring. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with graph traversal and coloring, which are important topics in AI. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also a less likely category, but possible as the paper deals with cutting graphs and constructing logic models for abstract figures.
